summary: why did kit say jon is in love with SOMEBODY? why? am so mad he gave nonsas another reason to bark about
question: why did kit say jon is in love with SOMEBODY? why? am so mad he gave nonsas another reason to bark about
answer:
Hi anon,

I believe this is the quote that bothers you

“The end of the world might be coming soon but atleast he is in love with somebody and knows who he is – and then comes a sledgehammer.”

-Kit Harrington (x)

So going by their tradition anti’s did find a way to flip things over yet again. Kit saying Jon is in love with somebody doesn’t mean he is being shady about who it actually is it’s more like FINALLY HE IS IN LOVE WITH SOMEBODY.

Unpopular opinion (maybe?!) Jon has never truly fallen in love with anyone be it Ygritte or Val. But this time he is indeed in love, after coming back from the dead & at a point in his life when he least expected LOVE to hit him it did. He fell in Love with Daenerys. 

Jon always felt an honor towards ygritte for being his first because he is a good man! By far Jon doesn’t have any romantic feelings for Val only that he thinks she is beautiful, & he is also weirdly attracted to Melisandre because she is described being very beautiful also carice van houten is gorgeous.

“I think he does, he does have that struggle, in that he is at the heart of it he is a man & as such he craves what men crave, which is the company of women. But I think whole of second season where he is talking to her (ygritte), being tempted by her & teased by her, it’s pretty hard not to look at that side of the things. He does have that struggle, he is tempted to run off like Mance Rayder did & joined the wildlings..”

-Kit Harrington (x)

This ☝️ It never happened in the books where Jon admits to ever love ygritte let alone “still love her”. This Mel & Jon conversation happens in a very different way in the books.

“I would bring back Robb Stark and his mother Catelyn just because I really miss Richard and Michelle who played them. Richard and I are still best mates. And Ygritte would come back of course. I think Jon’s never been happier than when he was with her - and I don’t think he ever will”

-Kit Harington.

Kit! We get it she is your wifey & you’d have to take her name or else no food for days.. But apart from that I kinda think yes, between the Jon before the Battle of the Wall who knew it’s impossible to impregnate the Wall vs the Jon who’ll find out that the greatest defence they had has been brought down by an undead Dragon being the broody goody Jon is, such an imminent danger is not going to allow him to be happy. He isn’t going to be the carefree boy hungry for glory anymore!

This is a man who is in Love with this woman, about to be a married man with the responsibility of the love of his life & his child, his family in perhaps the most dangerous time to have a family. It’s Jon’s melancholy not his reluctance that anti’s like to frame it into being.

I hope this helps nonny!
